Pinus gerardiana

   [8632.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Pinopsida:Pinaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names Ghilghoza pine, Nejan pine, Neoza pine
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8632

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is an evergreen somewhat branchy tree, reaching a
   height of 17-20 m or even 27 m and a girth of 2-2.6 m or up to 4 m.
   Crown usually deep, wide and open with long, erect branches, but crown
   narrower and shallower in dense forest. Bark very flaky, peeling to
   reveal light greyish-green patches. USE: It is cultivated for its
   edible seed. GROWING PERIOD: Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Chilgoza pine,
   Himalayan edible pine, Chilghoza, Chujin, Mirri, Ri. FURTHER INF: In
   eastern Afghanistan, northern Pakistan, Jammu-Kashmir and Tibet it can
   be found between 32-36Â°N at elevations from 2000 to 3600 m. It is a
   hardy tree, standing excessive drought and high winds. Endures severe
   cold in the winter.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Troup R 1921 pp 1090-1093 [FER, RAIN, TEMP, DEP, DRA, TEXT, LIG, USE]

